                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A <em>soul chain</em> is a <em>+1 striking @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.equipment-srd.Item.Spiked Chain]</em> that has become cursed after a forge-spurned used it to kill a creature and trap its soul. In the hands of a forge-spurned, a soul chain inflicts an additional @Damage[1d6[fire]] damage on a hit. Other creatures can use a <em>soul chain</em> as a standard <em>+1 striking spiked chain</em>. A soul chain fuses with its wielder the first time the wielder damages a living creature with the weapon. A character who dies while carrying a <em>soul chain</em> must attempt a @Check[type:will|dc:20] save; on a failure, they're immediately transformed into a forge-spurned. Carrying multiple <em>soul chains</em> doesn't increase the DC of the save, but the carrier must attempt the save once for each chain they carry.</p>"
